<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Challenge 4: Secrets in a Photo</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Challenges</a>
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="page-logo">

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>📸 Challenge 4: Secrets in a Photo</h1>
      <p class="desc">Every photo has a hidden "ID card" with invisible info. Time to be a digital detective!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="story-box">
        The security team intercepted a suspicious photo. It looks like a normal picture, but digital photos secretly carry <strong>metadata</strong> — the camera, the time, even GPS location! Download the photo and dig into its hidden data.
      </div>

      <a href="/challenge/4/download" class="download-btn">📥 Download Evidence Photo</a>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>🛠️ How to read a photo's secrets</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Search <strong>"EXIF viewer online"</strong> and upload the photo</li>
          <li>Or on Windows: right-click → Properties → Details</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Need a hint?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">Upload the photo to an online EXIF viewer. Look for the <code>Comment</code> field — the flag is hiding there!</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch4')">Submit Flag</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
